other_tests.findings: Normal liver morphology and signal on T2 weighted imaging; fat deposition in hepatic parenchyma; 0.7 cm enhancing lesion in caudate lobe likely focal nodular hyperplasia; multiple gallstones; distended gallbladder with pericholecystic fluid; tiny 4 mm gallbladder wall nodule consistent with a polyp; normal pancreatic and renal morphology.
